HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 215
BY REPRESENTATIVE DANA HENRY
A RESOLUTION
To designate April 29, 2026, as Hospital Day in Louisiana.
WHEREAS, Hospital Day is a celebration that serves as a reminder that hospitals in
Louisiana are cornerstones of the communities, and that hospitals serve people in every
community from all walks of life; and
WHEREAS, Hospital Day celebrates hospitals and the frontline caregivers who
support the health of their communities through dedication and compassionate care; and
WHEREAS, the theme for Hospital Day this year is "Advancing Louisiana's Health
Through Community Programs, Partnerships, and Innovations"; and
WHEREAS, hospitals and health systems in Louisiana play an integral role in
providing vital healthcare services to all residents of Louisiana, twenty-four hours a day,
seven days a week, three hundred sixty-five days a year, through acute care and specialty
hospital services; and
WHEREAS, hospitals today are multi-dimensional environments that offer every
medical specialty, and also focus on population health, prevention, and wellness; and
WHEREAS, in addition to providing critical healthcare services, Louisiana hospitals
and health systems are economic drivers in the state directly employing more than one
hundred thousand people with an annual payroll of more than seven and a half billion dollars
and contributing more than thirty-eight billion dollars to Louisiana's economy overall
through creating and supporting more than three hundred thousand direct and indirect jobs
statewide in industries such as construction and retail; and
